cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.SOC, cs.LG 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with social media traces and their integration into mobility models. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper proposes a hybrid model of human mobility. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is relevant as the paper discusses the impact of digital platforms and location-aware services on mobility models. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks) is relevant as the paper deals with human mobility flows and their prediction. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses a stacked regression procedure to integrate the social media data into the mobility model.
